  - m_Id: 20029729959936
    m_Localized: Business communication refers to the process by which organizations
      convey information and emotions through language, text, and behavior to achieve
      collaborative transactions and other business objectives. Its essence is value
      transmission and consensus building. It can be divided by audience into internal
      team collaboration and external customer public relations; by form into formal
      contracts and reports versus informal social interactions. The core focus is
      on reducing information disparities to facilitate the realization of goals.
