  - m_Id: 1464815850647552
    m_Localized: Procedures and precautions for signing contracts
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1464967034335232
    m_Localized: Common misunderstandings and solutions in contract writing
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1465100744552448
    m_Localized: Reference to model contracts and examples
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1466839837208576
    m_Localized: "1. Business Contract Concepts\r\n\u2022 Interest-driven: Core economic
      benefits (e.g., goods delivery/payment).\r\n\u2022 Adversarial: Balancing differing
      positions (e.g., supplier advance payment vs. buyer payment on delivery).\r\n\u2022
      Equitable: Win-win pursuit (e.g., \"Buyer \u2191order \u2192 Supplier 10% discount\").\r\n\r\n2.
      Basic Structure\r\n\u2022 Preamble: Title, number, date/location, parties'
      legal names/addresses.\r\n\u2022 Body: Key clauses\u2014\r\n- Subject matter:
      Item name/specs/quantity (\"Party A provides 10 units of Model A\").\r\n- Price:
      Unit/total price, payment method (\"Total: \xA51M, paid in 3 installments\").\r\n-
      Performance: Delivery time/place/acceptance criteria (\"Party B delivers to
      Party A's warehouse by Dec 31, 2024\").\r\n- Breach liability: Default scenarios/compensation
      (\"Late payment: 0.05% daily penalty\").\r\n\u2022 End: Copies, annex validity,
      signatures/seals.\r\n\r\n3. Clause Design Principles\r\n\u2022 Equal rights/obligations:
      E.g., \"Party A pays on time; Party B delivers on time.\"\r\n\u2022 Unambiguous
      language: Use data\u2014\"Delivery within 30 workdays after advance payment\"
      not \"ASAP.\"\r\n\u2022 Risk prevention: Address obstacles\u2014\"Force majeure
      exempts both parties.\"\r\n\r\n4. Key Clause Drafting\r\n\u2022 Quality: Acceptance
      criteria (\"Complies with GB/T1234-2020\").\r\n\u2022 Packaging: Form/cost
      bearer (\"Wooden crates; cost borne by Party B\").\r\n\u2022 Dispute resolution:
      Jurisdiction (\"Disputes submitted to Guangzhou Arbitration Commission\")."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1467317031563264
    m_Localized: "1. Signing Process\r\n1. Negotiation consensus (key terms: price/delivery).\r\n2.
      Drafting by party/professional.\r\n3. Review/modification (focus: legality/interest
      protection).\r\n4. Signing/filing: Authorized reps sign/seal; duplicate copies
      stored.\r\n\r\n2. Legal Compliance\r\n\u2022 Capacity: Natural persons \u226518;
      legal entities with valid business licenses.\r\n\u2022 Signing/sealing: Natural
      persons sign/fingerprint; entities use official/seal.\r\n\u2022 Annex validity:
      \"Annex [Technical Specs] is integral to this contract.\"\r\n\r\n3. Performance
      Risk Control\r\n\u2022 Tracking: Log key milestones (\"Party B provides tracking
      # within 24h of shipment\").\r\n\u2022 Change management: Written confirmation
      for modifications (\"Delivery extended to Jan 15, 2025 by mutual consent\").\r\n\u2022
      Dispute handling: Negotiate first \u2192 arbitration/litigation per contract."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1467537328992256
    m_Localized: "1. Common Pitfalls & Fixes\r\n\u2022 Vague payment: \"Party A pays
      after receiving goods\" \u2192 \"Party A pays 90% via bank transfer within
      10 workdays post-acceptance.\"\r\n\u2022 Missing breach terms: \"Default handled
      per Contract Law\" \u2192 \"Late delivery: 0.1% daily penalty; >30 days late:
      Party A may terminate + claim damages.\"\r\n\r\n2. Intercultural Contracts\r\n\u2022
      Language: Bilingual versions; Chinese prevails.\r\n\u2022 Governing law: \"This
      contract is governed by PRC law.\"\r\n\u2022 Cultural sensitivity: Avoid taboos
      (e.g., pork/alcohol in Middle East)."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1467751645343744
    m_Localized: "Sales Contract Template\r\nParty A (Seller): XX Co.\r\nParty B
      (Buyer): YY Co.\r\n\r\nI. Subject Matter\r\nParty B buys 50 laptops (Model
      A: Intel i5, 8GB RAM, 512GB SSD).\r\nUnit: \xA55,000; Total: \xA5250,000.\r\n\r\nII.
      Delivery\r\nParty A delivers to Party B's warehouse (XX Road, Tianhe, Guangzhou)
      by Dec 31, 2024.\r\nParty B inspects within 3 workdays per Annex I (Technical
      Specs).\r\n\r\nIII. Payment\r\nParty B pays \xA550,000 advance within 5 workdays
      of signing.\r\nBalance \xA5200,000 paid within 10 workdays post-acceptance.\r\n\r\nIV.
      Breach Liability\r\nLate delivery: 0.05% daily penalty on undelivered value.\r\nLate
      payment: 0.03% daily penalty on unpaid amount.\r\n\r\nV. Dispute Resolution\r\nNegotiate
      first \u2192 Guangzhou Arbitration Commission if unresolved.\r\n\r\nVI. Miscellaneous\r\nEffective
      upon signing/sealing; duplicate copies.\r\n\r\nParty A (Seal): XX Co.\r\nLegal
      Rep (Signature): XXX\r\nDate: Dec 1, 2024\r\n\r\nParty B (Seal): YY Co.\r\nLegal
      Rep (Signature): XXX\r\nDate: Dec 1, 2024"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1684607316553728
    m_Localized: 'Six Dynasties

      Book of Southern Qi: Account of Southeastern
      Barbarians: "The southern barbarians, diverse tribes establishing island states,
      offer treasures unmatched elsewhere. Mountains hide waters brimming with jewels.
      Merchant ships arrive from afar, goods converge in the southern regions, enriching
      Jiaozhou and Guangzhou, filling imperial coffers."

      Yin Ju''s Ode to
      Extraordinary Cloth and Preface: "In the second year of Taikang (281 CE), Teng
      Hou, General of Annam and Governor of Guangzhou, governed the south. I, then
      a minor official, witnessed the Great Qin (Rome) presenting treasures through
      our province. Among exquisite wonders, fire-resistant cloth was exceptional."

      Guangxiao
      Temple is where Bodhidharma, founder of Zen Buddhism, taught.

      Ge Hong''s
      Biographies of Deities: Huang Chuping of Danxi herded sheep as a boy. Meeting
      a Taoist, he attained enlightenment and became an immortal. (Today, Wong Tai
      Sin temples in Guangzhou, Foshan, and Hong Kong''s Kowloon attract worshippers
      and form bustling commercial districts for goods and fortune-telling.)'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1685206934253568
    m_Localized: 'Sui, Tang, and Five Dynasties

      Huaisheng Mosque, built in
      the High Tang, blends Chinese and West Asian architecture, documenting ancient
      foreign trade and relations with the Arab Empire.

      Tang Zhengxiong''s
      Miscellaneous Records of Panyu: "By the sea, ghost markets convene at midnight
      and disperse at cockcrow. Those who go often obtain exotic goods." (Note: This
      refers to illegal black markets, associated with darkness.)

      Hong Sheng
      Wang is an epithet for the South Sea God Zhu Rong. The cult emerged in the
      Sui dynasty; in 594 CE, Emperor Wen ordered a temple built near the sea at
      Nanhai Town. In 751 CE, the Tang granted him the title "King of Broad Profits."
      In 1041 CE, the Song renamed him "King of Vast Sagacity and Broad Profits."'
