      Poems IV: \"Dominating white blooms, plucked to cool summer's heat. In the
      land of Suxin, even Xun Yu's famed fragrance pales.\"\r\nNorthern Song Su Shen's
      Poem on Viewing Sugar Palm Trees at Puxian Pavilion with Mei Zhi: \"Cantonese
      merchants transplanted them westward\u2014gnarled trunks witness how many autumns!
      Honored by day, I return to admire them; next visit, I'll roam with Red Pine
      Immortals.\""
