      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1695425764552704
    m_Localized: "Teaware Placement: Electric kettle, small teapot, thimble-sized
      cups, tray, charcoal/electric stove on table to maintain water temperature.\r\nTea
      & Water: Oolong teas (e.g., Baiye Dancong, Shuixian, Huangdan). Preferred water:
      settled \"jar-core water,\" rainwater, snow water, spring/well water.\r\nBrewing:
      Boil water \u2192 scald teapot/cups \u2192 fill teapot 80% with leaves. \"Skim
      foam\": Remove impurities after pouring water. \"Lid shower\": Pour boiling
      water over teapot to enhance infusion.\r\nServing: \"Guanyu Patrols\": Pour
      tea in circular motion over cups for uniform strength. \"Hanxin Commands\":
      Distribute last drops evenly. Scald cups after each round.\r\nEtiquette: Host
      places all teaware near guests, accompanying throughout. Juniors stand to thank
      host, offer tea to others first, then sip slowly (palm outward), never taking
      center cup."
